snippet.textDisplay:
I think Jeremy Johns said it well when he mentioned that Finn’s story was a missed opportunity.
Instead of J.J. Undoing what Rian Johnson did with TLJ they should have rolled with the punches and used it.

Imagine the Resistance beaten down and lacking members to fight back. So what do our heroes do?
Finn determines to go set his fellow stormtroopers free by data mining the families and original names of all his fellow stormtroopers kidnapped as children like himself.
They go on a risky mission to recover this data from some archive. After retrieving it they spread it all over the imperial holonet causing a massive divide in the 1st Order forces.

Thru this impromptu recruitment drive the 1st Order turns on itself and the Resistance rises in ranks overwhelmingly out of nowhere in the eyes of their enemies.

Rey in the meantime is pulled between choosing Kylo or Finn. Kylo legitimately becomes the new villain of the saga, for better or worse, and attempts to secure his new empire, achieving what evil Anakin wanted all the way back in the prequels.
Rey feels him drawing her away from the light promising the same union Darth Vader offered his son in the clouds of Bespin.
She goes to confront him in an attempt to redeem his soul, effectively ending the fight with his transformation back to the light. Only Kylo, not matter how torn he is while feeling the pull back towards the light, he resists in the end fully embracing his fall.
Rey finally chooses Finn as a result, seeing the monster he truly is and engages in a final climactic battle.
She eventually overcomes Kylo and as he’s dying she holds his hand and he affirms he really had affection for her leaving Rey emotionally scarred over his death.

I think this would have been a much better road to travel instead of trying to undue the damage already done.

Just my opinion.
